g.text: Open Energy Playground is a projects that aims to make it easier to prototype smart energy services. On this
site you will find links to a number of tutorials for how to messure and analyse data from different devices.
You will find tutorials for how to set up servers that handle this data as well as tutorials for how to visualise
the data. In addition we provide a number of resources and tools such as live data from our testsites and a

OR GO DIRECTLY TO OUR GETTING STARTED TUTORIAL
Open Energy Playground provices a set of collected data as well as an tutoral to the energy use of common
electrical devices in you home. This will enable you to quickly form an understanding of how different
aspects of a devices funtional properties can be messured and indentified. Click on either of the devices
below to find out more about how they work.
Open Energy Playground provices a number of libraries for collecting data through either electricity meter,
building automation systems and smart plugs. We also provide exampes of how to create your own smart
sensors based on differnt IoT chips. In addition to this we also offers a number of scripts form polling data
from different webresources such as for example your energy company or the national grid.
Open Energy Playground offers a number of docker containers where open source software for collecting,
processing and servicing data resources to different apps are avalible for easy installtion on either your PC
or your Raspberry PI. Below you can find links to the docker setup tutorial as well as the tools inside the setup.

text.tspan: Open Energy Playground will also provide a number of guides for setting up hackatons and for using the
tools in creative workshops. In addition tools will also be provided for collecting and processing user data
from test instalations as well as tools for preforming QDA style analysis of the data to evaluate the effect of
apps on for example user behaviors.
